Introduction

MOMOLAND is a six-member girl group formed by MLD Entertainment through the 2016 reality show Finding Momoland. The show's winners were Hyebin, Yeonwoo, Jane, Nayun, JooE, Ahin, and Nancy, who served as the seven original members of the group and debuted on November 10, 2016 with the release of the EP "Welcome to MOMOLAND". In 2017, MOMOLAND became a nine-member group when Daisy and Taeha were added to the line-up, making their debut with the release of "Wonderful Love", on April 26, 2017.

Eventually, MOMOLAND lost a few members as both Taeha and Yeonwoo left the group in 2019 to make a new start, and Daisy was kicked out in 2020, leaving MOMOLAND with six members.

As MOMOLAND's contract with MLD Entertainment was coming to an end, it was announced on January 27, 2023, that the members all departed from the label, which led to fans thinking that the group had disbanded. However, JooE claimed that it wasn't the case and, because of that claim, it was safe to say that the group was only on a hiatus. The state of the group was further confirmed on April 10, 2025, when it was reported that MOMOLAND had signed with Inyeon Entertainment and will be resuming their activities as a group.
